\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 16. S. ilicifolia} Willd.,{\i  Enum. Pl. Hort. Berol.} 606 (1809). Glabrous or very sparsely hairy perennial 20-40 cm, with dense short glandular papillae at least on upper part of stem. Leaves 15-45 × c. 8 mm, linear or lanceolate, with 6-10 divaricate lateral spines. Verticillasters 3-6, many-flowered, more or less distant. Lower bracts 10-15 × 12-16 mm, about equalling calyx, ovate to cordate-ovate, coarsely incise-dentate and spiny. Calyx 5-8 mm, with a ring of hairs inside. Corolla 8-9 mm, pale yellow, exceeding calyx. {\i Dry, rocky or gravelly soils. • E. Spain.} Hs.
